      "type": "subsection",
      "title": "3. Architecture",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "typography",
          "html": "<p>The analytics service exposes REST endpoints backed by MongoDB aggregation pipelines. Domain services write operational data; analytics-service reads and transforms it for dashboards and APIs.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "mermaidDiagram",
          "title": "High-level system view",
          "chart": "flowchart LR\n  orderService[order-service] --> commerceDB[(commerce)]\n  productService[product-service] --> commerceDB\n  paymentService[payment-service] --> commerceDB\n  reviewService[review-service] --> commerceDB\n  commerceDB --> analyticsService[analytics-service]\n  analyticsService --> apiGateway[API Gateway]\n  apiGateway --> client[Client Apps]"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "subsection",
      "title": "6. Implemented analytics APIs",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "basicTable",
          "title": "Pipeline endpoints",
          "headers": [
            "Endpoint",
            "Stages",
            "Purpose"
          ],
          "rows": [
            [
              "GET /api/analytics/orders/enriched",
              "$match → $lookup → $project",
              "Enriched orders"
            ],
            [
              "GET /api/analytics/products/ratings",
              "$lookup → $unwind → $group",
              "Product rating summary"
            ],
            [
              "GET /api/analytics/payments/revenue",
              "$match → $group",
              "Revenue by status"
            ],
            [
              "POST /api/analytics/pipeline/execute",
              "native stages JSON",
              "Raw pipeline executor"
            ]
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "codeSnippet",
          "filename": "enriched-orders.pipeline.json",
          "language": "json",
          "code": "[\n  { \"$match\": { \"status\": \"COMPLETED\" } },\n  { \"$lookup\": { \"from\": \"products\", \"localField\": \"productId\", \"foreignField\": \"_id\", \"as\": \"product\" } },\n  { \"$unwind\": \"$product\" },\n  { \"$project\": { \"orderId\": 1, \"productName\": \"$product.name\", \"amount\": 1 } }\n]"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "contentCard",
      "subheading": "7. Raw pipeline executor",
      "paragraphs": [
        "<p>POST <code>/api/analytics/pipeline/execute</code> accepts native stage JSON so engineers can test pipelines from Compass or mongosh before promoting them to typed endpoints.</p>"
      ],
